6.2 

Runtime Scenario UC-01 — Initialize Network

This describes the dynamic behavior visualized in your sequence diagram.

Purpose

Create a new simulation with a chosen topology (ring, grid, random), allocate N nodes, and register the simulation for further use (UC-02…UC-10).

Participating Components
UI (Config & Control View)
SimulationControlService
SimulationManagement (Registry + Context)
SimulationCore (Engine + Nodes)

Remarks
The entire interaction is synchronous until the engine is created. After engine creation, all further behavior becomes event-driven.
No nodes communicate yet; MessagingPort is idle until UC-03 (Start Simulation).
No metrics exist yet; visualization only shows the static topology.


-------------------------------------


6.3 Runtime Scenario UC-03 — Start Simulation
Once the network is initialized and an algorithm is selected

Notable Properties

Fully asynchronous
No blocking calls
Event-driven execution
UI responsiveness unaffected by simulation load

------------------------------------------------------------


Runtime Scenario UC-04 — Pause / Resume Simulation
(not mentioned in doc)
Pause
UI → SimulationControlService: pauseSimulation(id)
ControlService → Engine: dispatch Pause event
Nodes stop processing new incoming messages (event loop suspended)
Metrics/visualization continue to operate on the frozen state

Resume
UI → ControlService: resumeSimulation(id)
Engine resumes message processing
Nodes continue algorithm execution



----------------------------------------------------------


6.5 Runtime Scenario UC-05 — Stop Simulation
UI → ControlService: stopSimulation(id)
Engine receives Stop event
Nodes finish remaining steps and shut down cleanly
Final metrics snapshot is produced
Visualization switches to “final” mode

---------------------------------------------------

6.6 Runtime Scenario UC-06 — Visualization
Triggered whenever SimulationEvents are emitted by nodes.
Flow
Node → EventBus: SimulationEvent(type, nodeId, ...)
Visualization module receives event
Visualization → UI: push update via WebSocket
UI updates the rendered graph in <200ms (Quality SC9 & SC11)


---------------------------------------------------------
6.7 Runtime Scenario UC-07 — View Metrics

UI → SimulationControlService: getMetrics(simId)
ControlService → MetricsCollector
Metrics returned synchronously (snapshot)
UI displays charts/numbers
Metrics are computed continuously via event listeners and do not affect node timing.

------------------------------------------------------
6.8 Runtime Scenario UC-08 — Save / Load Configuration
Save
UI → ControlService: getCurrentConfig(simId)
Control returns DTO SimulationConfig
UI writes file (JSON/TXT)

Load
UI loads file → ControlService: loadConfig(config)
SimulationManagement creates new Simulation+Engine
UI receives new SimulationId

-----------------------------------------------------
6.9 Runtime Scenario UC-09 — Export Run Data
UI → ControlService: exportRunData(simId, format)
ControlService collects events/metrics from EventBus archives
Returns byte[] to UI for saving

-------------------------------------------------------------

6.10 Runtime Scenario UC-10 — View Errors/Logs
UI → ControlService: getLogs(simId, filter)
Logs returned synchronously
UI displays them (no side effects)

















